PYTHON DAY 13 - MULTIPLE ATTRIBUTES & MULTIPLE METHODS

A class can have multiple attributes and multiple methods.

Example:

class Employee:

    def __init__(self, name, salary):
        self.name = name
        self.salary = salary

    def show_details(self):
        print(self.name)
        print(self.salary)

    def work(self):
        print(self.name, "is working")

employee1 = Employee("Ishu", 25000)

employee1.show_details()
employee1.work()

Output:

Ishu
25000
Ishu is working

Important:

Attributes:
name
salary

Methods:
show_details()
work()

Object:
employee1
